It followed repeated revelations that Williams had lied about his personal involvement in stories, including being hit by an RPG over Iraq.

NBC, which said he had violated the trust of their viewers, suspended Williams for six months without pay. He is one month in to the punishment.

In his absence, Holt has managed to keep ratings steady at the Nightly News program. 

